THE VIDEO IS NARRATED BY RON CLARK, AND HE IS TELLING HIS DAUGHTER JAMILLA CLARK ABOUT GROWING UP LIVING IN THE LIBRARY.
LIBRARIANS IN NEW YORK OFTEN LIVED IN THE LIBRARIES WITH THEIR FAMILIES.
RON'S DAD, JARROD, WAS A LIBRARIAN.
GROWING UP, RON THOUGHT THAT HE WAS RICH.
AFTER PROCLAIMING THAT AT THE DINNER TABLE, HIS PARENTS TOLD HIM THEY WERE ACTUALLY POOR.
HOWEVER, ONCE RON'S DAD GOT A JOB AT THE LIBRARY, HE BECAME THE "KEEPER" OF THE "TEMPLE OF KNOWLEDGE."
OTHER PUBLIC LIBRARIES OFTEN HAD GUM OR DIRT ON THE FLOOR.
HOWEVER, RON'S DAD KEPT THE LIBRARY EXTREMELY CLEAN AND WAXED BOTH THE FLOORS AND THE TOPS OF THE SHELVES.
WHEN RON FIRST MOVED IN TO THE LIBRARY, HE WAS ASHAMED.
HE WAS THE KID THAT LITERALLY "LIVED IN THE LIBRARY!
HOWEVER, HE EVENTUALLY CAME TO FIND THE LIBRARY AN AMAZING PLACE.
RON HAD TO BE QUIET DURING THE DAY WHEN THE LIBRARY WAS OPEN.
HOWEVER, AT NIGHT AFTER THE LIBRARY CLOSED RON COULD RUN AROUND AND BE AS LOUD AS HE WANTED!
IF HE HAD ANY QUESTIONS RON COULD JUST GO DOWNSTAIRS AND FIND A BOOK AND READ UNTIL LATE AT NIGHT (3 IN THE MORNING).
RON WAS THE FIRST PERSON IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL, LET ALONE GO TO COLLEGE!
HE SHOWED HIS DAD HIS CLASSROOM WITH HIS NAME IN FRONT: "PROFESSOR CLARK."
HIS DAD JUST LOOKED AT HIM, BUT RON KNEW HIS FATHER WANTED HIM TO ACHIEVE MORE THAN HE DID, AND TO GO FARTHER IN LIFE.
RON IS TELLING HIS DAUGHTER JACINDA ABOUT HOW GROWING UP HE LIVED IN A LIBRARY.
RON'S DAD, JARROD, GOT A JOB AS A LIBRARIAN
IN THE 50S, MANY LIBRARIANS AND LIBRARY CUSTODIANS LIVED IN THEIR LIBRARIES.
WHEN RON WAS YOUNGER, HE THOUGHT HE WAS RICH, UNTIL HIS PARENTS TOLD HIM THEY WERE ACTUALLY POOR.
HOWEVER, ONCE JARROD GOT HIS JOB AS THE LIBRARY CUSTODIAN, HE MOVED INTO THE LIBRARY WITH HIS WIFE AND SON, RON.
AT FIRST RON WAS EMBARRASSED BECAUSE HE WAS THE KID THAT LITERALLY "LIVED IN THE LIBRARY."
RON NEVER WANTED TO HAVE FRIENDS OVER.
DURING THE DAY, WHEN THE LIBRARY WAS OPEN, RON HAD TO BE QUIET.
HOWEVER, AT NIGHT, AFTER THE LIBRARY CLOSED, RON WAS THE ONLY CHILD IN THE BUILDING.
HE COULD RUN AROUND AND YELL.
WHENEVER HE HAD A QUESTION, RON WOULD JUST GO DOWN TO THE LIBRARY TO GET A BOOK.
HE WOULD READ UNTIL 3 IN THE MORNING.
RON'S DAD WAS A SPECIAL CUSTODIAN.
WHILE MANY LIBRARIES HAD GUM AND DIRTY FLOORS, RON'S DAD KEPT HIS LIBRARY IMPECCABLE.
IN ADDITION TO CLEANING AND WAXING THE FLOORS, JARROD WAXED THE TOP OF THE SHELVES.
JARROD WANTED RON TO ACHIEVE MORE THAN HE DID.
NONE OF RON'S FAMILY HAD EVEN GRADUATED HIGH SCHOOL.
RON WAS THE FIRST IN HIS FAMILY TO GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL AND ATTEND UNIVERSITY.
EVENTUALLY, RON BECAME A UNIVERSITY PROFESSOR.
HE SHOWED HIS FATHER THE NAMEPLATE ON HIS DOOR THAT READ "PROFESSOR CLARK."
JARROD WAS QUIET, BUT RON COULD SEE THE PRIDE IN HIS EYES.
